dias, cryptorchidism). Reduction in T levels during foetal development subsequently lower levels of its metabolite DHT lead also to impaired growth of the perineum with reduced anogential distance (AGD) (Bowman et al. 2003).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:32:46 +0000 2026"}